Edna Mae Wilson https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edna_Mae_Wilson 0 Edna Mae Wilson (1880–1960) was an American silent film actress. Signed by the Thanhouser Company based in New Rochelle, New York in 1913, she starred in about 15 films between 1913 and 1920, sometimes in only one short film a year and often credited alongside William Garwood. She died in New York on July 23, 1960. Edna_Mae_Wilson ( 1880 – 1960 ) was an_American_silent_film_actress .
